title: Improve AppLock code of no-xposed version A LOT

Improve AppLock code of no-xposed version A LOT

Checking for event.getSource().getWindow() == null filters out the window state changes when the app hasn't fully started yet, thus the issue with apps not launching after first unlock is now fixed. Also, this is the 1000th commit! Yay!

title: MaxLock - No Xposed Implementation
message:
MaxLock - No Xposed Implementation

This is a mostly stable, but not fully finished implementation of MaxLock which doesn't require root or Xposed and therefore also works on Android Nougat and O (tested on Preview!). It uses an accessibility service to monitor window state changes, and also automatically relocks if killed (and restarted). Further modifications, maybe even using root, will hopefully improve the reliability and security of this implementation.
